**1. Use Case Table**

| User Story | Use Case |
| --- | --- |
| **Healthcare Professional** | Tracks disease hotspots so that resources can be allocated effectively.<br>**Precondition:** Outbreak has begun.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides real-time updates on outbreak hotspots, allowing the healthcare professional to allocate resources efficiently.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If no hotspots are detected, the system notifies the healthcare professional. |
| **Healthcare Professional** | Evaluates intervention effectiveness so that data-driven decisions can be made.<br>**Precondition:** Interventions have been implemented.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides metrics on intervention effectiveness, enabling the healthcare professional to make informed adjustments.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If interventions are ineffective, the system alerts the healthcare professional. |
| **Community Leader** | Communicates risks effectively so that community remains informed and engaged.<br>**Precondition:** Risk levels change.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides clear, tailored risk communications, enabling the community leader to engage residents and maintain trust.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If risks are high, the system triggers automated emergency communication protocols. |
| **Community Leader** | Understands urban design impact so that evidence-based policies can be advocated for.<br>**Precondition:** Urban planning proposals are under review.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides data-driven insights on how urban design affects disease dynamics, allowing the community leader to advocate for informed policies.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If high-risk areas are identified, the system alerts the community leader. |
| **Urban Planner** | Evaluates urban form impact so that resilient cities can be designed.<br>**Precondition:** Urban planning proposals are under review.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system simulates disease spread dynamics under various urban forms, enabling the urban planner to design resilient cities.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If high-risk areas are identified, the system triggers automated notifications to urban planners. |
| **Urban Planner** | Optimizes mobility patterns so that disease dissemination can be minimized.<br>**Precondition:** Mobility data is available.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides mobility pattern analysis and optimization suggestions, allowing the urban planner to minimize disease dissemination.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If mobility patterns are inefficient, the system triggers automated recommendations for improvement. |
| **Technologist** | Validates new tools so that stakeholders' needs are met.<br>**Precondition:** New tools have been developed.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides user feedback and performance metrics on new tools, enabling the technologist to validate their effectiveness.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If tools are ineffective, the system triggers automated retesting and refinement. |
| **Technologist** | Integrates technology into modeling so that model usability is enhanced.<br>**Precondition:** Technological solutions are available.<br>**Main Success Scenario:** The system provides seamless integration of technological tools into Agent-Based Social Simulation modeling, enhancing model usability for all stakeholders.<br>**Alternative Paths:** If integration is unsuccessful, the system triggers automated troubleshooting and optimization. |

